    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-10T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-10T04:00:00-05:00" n="347"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10013: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Swatow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ketcham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Swatow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-10T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 10, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 10—2:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegrams September 6, 8 and 9,<note n="17" xml:id="d347fn17"
                        >None printed.</note> describing shelling and bombing of Swatow and
                    subsequent meeting of the Consular Corps, I feel that bombardment of city which
                    contains nothing of military importance excepting for a few machine gun <pb
                        facs="0327" n="319" xml:id="pg_319"/> emplacements, constitutes a grave
                    danger to American and other foreign lives and property to say nothing of
                    Chinese civilian population which latter has already suffered considerable
                    casualties. Japanese attacks were without warning and Mayor’s office and police
                    headquarters both purely civilian organizations situated in center of city were
                    deliberately singled out for air bombing attacks and both were struck. American
                    and foreign homes and business interests are scattered throughout the city
                    particularly near the water front and any bombarding or shelling seriously
                    endangers them. Standard Oil Company as reported in my telegram September 9 [<hi
                        rend="italic">8</hi>], 5 [<hi rend="italic">3</hi>] p.m.<note n="18"
                        xml:id="d347fn18">Not printed.</note> received bomb and shell fragments in
                    attack of September 8th and a devastating fire could easily have occurred. Two
                    bombs struck within 2 or 3 hundred yards of Company’s property. In view of the
                    foregoing it is respectfully suggested that Department and Embassy may consider
                    it desirable to protest against continued bombardment Swatow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ketcham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
